# src/components/ - Reusable React Components

## Purpose
Shared React components used across pages. Data-driven, not coupled to specific calculators.

## Organization

```
src/components/
├── layout/              # Page structure (Header, Footer, etc.)
│   ├── Header.tsx
│   ├── Footer.tsx
│   ├── StickyNav.tsx
│   └── ...
├── calculators/         # Calculator-specific components
│   ├── CalculatorLayout.tsx    # Main wrapper (reusable for ANY calculator)
│   ├── InputGroup.tsx
│   ├── ResultBox.tsx
│   ├── FAQAccordion.tsx
│   ├── RelatedTools.tsx
│   ├── BreadcrumbNav.tsx
│   └── ...
├── common/              # Generic, reusable components
│   ├── AdPlaceholder.tsx
│   ├── SchemaMarkup.tsx
│   └── ...
└── sections/            # Page sections (not reused)
    ├── HeroSection.tsx
    ├── ToolGrid.tsx
    └── ...
```

## Component Pattern

Every component must:

1. **Have a clear prop interface**
```tsx
interface InputGroupProps {
  label: string;
  type: 'number' | 'currency' | 'percentage';
  value: number;
  onChange: (value: number) => void;
  min?: number;
  max?: number;
  placeholder?: string;
  error?: string;
}

export function InputGroup({ label, type, value, onChange, ...props }: InputGroupProps) {
  // Component
}
```

2. **Use TypeScript strict mode**
```tsx
// YES - explicit types
const formatValue = (value: number): string => {
  return value.toFixed(2);
};

// NO - implicit any
const formatValue = (value) => {
  return value.toFixed(2);
};
```

3. **No inline styles** (use Tailwind className)
```tsx
// YES
<div className="px-4 py-2 rounded bg-white">
  Content
</div>

// NO
<div style={{ padding: "8px 16px", borderRadius: "4px" }}>
  Content
</div>
```

4. **Use clsx for conditional classes**
```tsx
import clsx from 'clsx';

<button className={clsx(
  'px-4 py-2 rounded transition',
  isActive ? 'bg-blue-500 text-white' : 'bg-gray-200'
)}>
  {label}
</button>
```

## Key Components

### CalculatorLayout

**File:** `calculators/CalculatorLayout.tsx`

Wrapper for all calculator pages. Takes tool config + content as props.

```tsx
interface CalculatorLayoutProps {
  tool: Tool;
  content: ContentData;
}

export function CalculatorLayout({ tool, content }: CalculatorLayoutProps) {
  return (
    <>
      <Header />
      <BreadcrumbNav category={tool.category} toolName={tool.name} />

      <main>
        <HeroSection h1={tool.h1} description={content.intro} />
        <CalculatorWidget tool={tool} />
        <AdPlaceholder />

        <section>
          <h2>How It Works</h2>
          <p>{content.howItWorks}</p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2>FAQ</h2>
          <FAQAccordion faqs={content.faqs} />
        </section>

        <section>
          <RelatedTools slugs={tool.relatedTools} />
        </section>
      </main>

      <SchemaMarkup tool={tool} content={content} />
      <Footer />
    </>
  );
}
```

**Key benefit:** One component handles all 50+ calculators (just swap props).

### InputGroup

**File:** `calculators/InputGroup.tsx`

Reusable input component with validation + error display.

```tsx
export function InputGroup({ label, value, onChange, error, ...props }: InputGroupProps) {
  return (
    <div className="mb-4">
      <label className="block mb-1 font-semibold">{label}</label>
      <input
        type="number"
        value={value}
        onChange={(e) => onChange(parseFloat(e.target.value))}
        className={clsx(
          'w-full px-3 py-2 border rounded',
          error ? 'border-red-500' : 'border-gray-300'
        )}
        {...props}
      />
      {error && <p className="text-red-500 text-sm mt-1">{error}</p>}
    </div>
  );
}
```

### ResultBox

**File:** `calculators/ResultBox.tsx`

Displays formatted results (currency, percentage, number).

```tsx
interface ResultBoxProps {
  label: string;
  value: number;
  format: 'currency' | 'percentage' | 'number';
}

export function ResultBox({ label, value, format }: ResultBoxProps) {
  let displayValue: string;
  if (format === 'currency') {
    displayValue = new Intl.NumberFormat('en-US', {
      style: 'currency',
      currency: 'USD',
    }).format(value);
  } else if (format === 'percentage') {
    displayValue = `${value.toFixed(2)}%`;
  } else {
    displayValue = value.toFixed(2);
  }

  return (
    <div className="p-4 bg-blue-50 rounded border border-blue-200">
      <p className="text-gray-600 text-sm">{label}</p>
      <p className="text-2xl font-bold text-blue-600">{displayValue}</p>
    </div>
  );
}
```

## Testing Components

Before committing:

```bash
npm run lint              # Check no TypeScript errors
npm run type-check       # Verify strict types
```

**Manual testing:**
1. Load page with component
2. Check PropTypes warnings (none expected)
3. Test on mobile (320px, 768px, 1440px)
4. Verify accessibility (keyboard nav, screen reader)

## Performance

- **No heavy imports in component file** (lazy load if needed)
- **Memoize if rendering expensive children** (optional, measure first)
- **Debounce onChange callbacks** (if many quick updates expected)

```tsx
import { useCallback } from 'react';

export function InputGroup({ onChange, ...props }) {
  const handleChange = useCallback((value) => {
    // Debounce or batch updates if needed
    onChange(value);
  }, [onChange]);

  return <input onChange={(e) => handleChange(e.target.value)} />;
}
```

## Common Mistakes

❌ **Hardcoding strings in components**
- Pass as props or load from config

❌ **Mixing layout + data**
- InputGroup should not fetch calculator data (props only)

❌ **No TypeScript interfaces**
- Every component needs explicit PropTypes or interface

✅ **Props-driven design**
- Component behavior = props, not internal state

✅ **Single responsibility**
- InputGroup handles input validation (not calculation)

